<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="mad-adj">mad <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /mæd/    美 /mæd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>发疯的；发狂似的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The fans <strong>went mad with joy</strong> because, in their mind, the right team had won. 
球迷们欣喜若狂，因为在他们看来，应获胜的队赢了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[非正式用语] 愚蠢的；狂妄的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Surely no one would be mad enough to fly in this weather. 
肯定没有人会这么疯狂，敢在这样的天气飞行。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[非正式用语] [不用于名词前] 很生气的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mother got <strong>mad with</strong> me for watching <strong>TV</strong> so much.
我看电视太多了，惹得妈妈大发脾气。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What are you so <strong>mad about</strong>?
什么事让你火气这么大？</p></div>

<h4 id="4-crazy">4.★ <strong>[非正式用语] 狂热的；着迷的 (crazy)：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>(be) mad about / on sb / sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My daughter is mad on Robbie Williams.
我女儿对罗比·威廉姆斯非常着迷。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is mad about computer games.
他迷上了电脑游戏。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>madly  /'mædli/ adv   </p></div>